We are home!!! üòç As I mentioned recently, I'm taking time at the moment to really think about my goals for next year. I will be doing an Instagram story explaining a bit more about this, but I set my main goal and then I work out how I‚Äôm going to GET IT DONE!‚Å£
‚Å£
I don‚Äôt set a generic goal, I make it really specific, and then plan in detail. If I say I‚Äôm going to get stronger, I then figure out: how many times a week I‚Äôm going to train, which program I‚Äôm going to do, what time I‚Äôm going to train, who‚Äôs going to look after Arna while I‚Äôm at the gym and when is the best time to eat around my workouts. Every day this needs extra planning too - I need to have all my gym clothes ready, my water bottle and my bag. I make sure I have EVERYTHING I need to be successful, rather than having a vague goal and just hoping somehow I'll get there. ‚Å£
‚Å£

Find the exercise that's right for YOU!!! If you‚Äôve been following me for a while, you might already know that I‚Äôm not a big fan of running. In my opinion, there‚Äôs nothing wrong with running - it just doesn‚Äôt work for me. I don‚Äôt enjoy it and I don‚Äôt feel great afterwards. If you are doing any type of exercise because you think it will get results, but you actually don‚Äôt enjoy it, I would recommend changing it up.  Mostly because if you don't like it, you're less likely to keep doing it. ‚Å£
‚Å£
From my experience as a personal trainer, you are more likely to stick to an exercise program if you enjoy it and feel GREAT after - that‚Äôs why BBG workouts are 28 minutes - I try and keep them fun and fast. The LISS (low-intensity steady state) workouts in BBG are a chance for you to do a form of exercise that you really enjoy. ‚Å£
I recommend starting with walking if you are a fitness beginner because I find it's most achievable for many women when starting out. I love walking because it‚Äôs something I can do with Arna in a stroller and it gets us both out of the house. If I'm not able to get out for a walk with Arna, I'll walk on the treadmill and watch Netflix! üòÅ‚Å£
‚Å£
If you want to try different types of LISS, I recommend hiking, cycling (outdoors or on a spin-cycle bike), swimming - or anything that can be done at a steady state for 30-45 minutes. ‚Å£
‚Å£
Finding out what works for YOU is KEY. I really want women to train and start their health and fitness journey from a place of self-love, not doing a form of exercise they dislike because they feel like they ‚Äúhave to‚Äù. Having a positive relationship with yourself and your training is SO important, so if you actually LOVE running, keep doing it! ‚Å£
But if you haven‚Äôt found what you love yet, keep trying until you do! And the #BBGcommunity will be there to support you the whole way! üí™üèºüôåüèº

OMG I DID ITüôåüôåüôåüôå I‚ÄôM SO PROUD!! ‚Å£If you've been following my journey since having Arna, you'll know that I have been working towards a goal of 15 pull-ups by December! ‚Å£
‚Å£
To be honest - I don‚Äôt actually care that it‚Äôs 15 pull-ups, because at the end of the day, it‚Äôs not about how many pull-ups I can do, or how far I can run or how high I can jump - the fact is I showed up for myself EVERY SINGLE DAY. I put in the work, and I did this for ME, just to prove to myself that I could. By regaining my strength, I also regained my CONFIDENCE. ‚Å£
‚Å£
This has actually been a HUGE learning process for me, because I never thought I would be a "beginner". From being such an active kid to becoming a personal trainer, there was never a day in my life when I wasn‚Äôt active, so I literally never thought I wouldn‚Äôt be able to move the way I was used to moving, but that‚Äôs exactly where I was. ‚Å£
‚Å£
#BBGcommunity, I could not have done this without you. Your support, your inspiring stories - I am where I am today because of you. It's so important for all of us to continue to set NEW goals throughout our health and fitness journeys. Ladies, I want to know - what YOU are working towards? Share your goals in the comments below!
